Austrian shares fail to break above 1 , 400 points . Austria ' s ATX index took a shot at the 1 , 400 level on Monday before slipping back to end just 0 . 5 percent higher , and traders said the market was unlikely to breach key psychological resistance this week . The blue - chip index finished at 1 , 393 . 90 , 7 . 05 points up on the day but below an intra - day high of 1 , 400 . 51 . Last Wednesday the ATX set a record closing high of 1 , 399 . 4 . " Quite simply , Vienna does not want to go above 1 , 400 points , " a trader said , adding that fresh sell orders were taking the steam out of every rally . Index heavyweights were particularly vulnerable to selling , market participants said . They forecast the ATX would hover around current levels until the expiry of July ATX futures on Friday . July ATX future finished five points at 1 , 402 . " Some of the local banks seem to have a vested interest in lower prices , " a trader said . Overall 13 ATX shares finished higher , seven lower and one unchanged . Luxury hosiery maker Wolford , which presents its 1996 / 1997 results next week , was the top gainer . Its shares climbed 50 schillings , or 4 . 07 percent , to 1 , 280 . Steelmaker VA Stahl and brewer BBAG were also among the gainers . Creditanstalt ordinary and preferred shares firmed as investors speculated on a favourable exchange ratio for shares in new owner Bank Austria , dealers said . " A spread is forming of around 35 percent in the preference shares and 30 percent in the ordinaries , " said one . Moody ' s decision to downgrade Bank Austria ' s long - term credit rating and upgrade Creditanstalt ' s was widely expected , dealers noted . Utilities EVN and Verbund led the decliners . Lower Austrian firm EVN ended 36 schillings , or 2 . 28 percent , down at 1 , 544 . The broad - based Vienna bourse index closed 2 . 11 points up at 502 . 37 . - - Vienna newsroom , + 431 531 12257 
